      <title>Labor Oral Histories</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>Dr. Troy Smith interviewed individuals regarding work performed in shirt factories and on tobacco farms as part of a Labor Oral History project for the Upper Cumberland Humanities and Social Sciences Institute. Participants discussed issues including working conditions in factories and in the fields on farms. Interviews describe a typical day of meeting production goals and various responsibilities in garment factories, preparing land for planting and the harvesting process, relationships with co-workers, and minimum wages paid.</abstract>
